
### Question 1: Basic Commands
**Q: What command would you use to list all S3 buckets in your AWS account?**

A. `aws s3 ls`

B. `aws s3 mb`

C. `aws s3 cp`

D. `aws s3 rm`

### Question 2: Configuration
**Q: Which command is used to configure the AWS CLI with your AWS credentials and default settings?**

A. `aws configure`

B. `aws init`

C. `aws setup`

D. `aws install`

### Question 3: File Transfer
**Q: How would you copy a file named `myfile.txt` from your local machine to the home directory of an EC2 instance using SCP, assuming your key file is named `my-key.pem` and the EC2 instance public DNS is `ec2-203-0-113-25.compute-1.amazonaws.com`?**

A. `scp myfile.txt ec2-203-0-113-25.compute-1.amazonaws.com:/home/ec2-user -i my-key.pem`

B. `scp -i my-key.pem myfile.txt ec2-user@ec2-203-0-113-25.compute-1.amazonaws.com:~`

C. `scp ec2-user@ec2-203-0-113-25.compute-1.amazonaws.com:/home/ec2-user myfile.txt -i my-key.pem`

D. `scp -i my-key.pem ec2-user@ec2-203-0-113-25.compute-1.amazonaws.com:~ myfile.txt`

### Question 4: Validating Templates
**Q: What is the correct AWS CLI command to validate a CloudFormation template stored locally in a file named `template.yaml`?**

A. `aws cloudformation validate-template --template-body file://template.yaml`

B. `aws cloudformation check-template --template-file template.yaml`

C. `aws cloudformation validate-template --template-url file://template.yaml`

D. `aws cloudformation check-template --template-body template.yaml`

### Question 5: IAM Users
**Q: Which AWS CLI command would you use to list all IAM users in your AWS account?**

A. `aws iam describe-users`

B. `aws iam get-users`

C. `aws iam list-users`

D. `aws iam show-users`

### Answer Key:
1. A
2. A
3. B
4. A
5. C

